<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="b1945_05_06_an_RandRose"><teiHeader><fileDesc> <titleStmt> <title>Von <persName key="WittgensteinLudwig" role="sender" full="yes">Ludwig Wittgenstein</persName> an <persName key="RandRose" role="recipient" full="yes">Rose Rand</persName>, 6. 5. 1945</title> <author>Wittgenstein, Ludwig</author> </titleStmt> <editionStmt n="bw2"> <edition>2. Auflage</edition> </editionStmt> <publicationStmt> <p>Ludwig Wittgenstein: Gesamtbriefwechsel, 2. Auflage</p> </publicationStmt> <sourceDesc default="false"> <p>Abschrift McGuinness.</p> </sourceDesc> </fileDesc><encodingDesc><p>TEI P5</p></encodingDesc><revisionDesc><list type="simple"><item>2010/05/15: Added to the collection</item><item>2018/12: Added to Innsbruck Correspondence Edition</item></list></revisionDesc></teiHeader><text><body><div type="transcript" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"> <div type="address" org="uniform" sample="complete" part="N"> <p rend="right">Trinity College </p> <p rend="right">Cambridge </p> <p rend="right">6.5.45. </p> </div> <div type="maintext" org="uniform" sample="complete" part="N"> <p rend="left">Dear Miss Rand,</p> <p rend="indent">Thank you for your letter dated April 22<hi rend="superscript">nd</hi>. You have, in my opinion, no chance whatever of getting money from a university. A ›Fellowship‹ is, of course, out of the question; but so, I believe, is a Studentship, or even a Research Grant.</p> <p rend="indent">I should advise you to leave this idea <hi rend="underline">completely</hi> out of your plans &amp; to resign yourself to doing work which, though it may not attract you as much as university work, will perhaps be more useful.</p> <p rend="indent">Yours sincerely </p> <p rend="indent">L. Wittgenstein</p> </div> </div></body></text></TEI>